cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with the problem of electing a committee subject to constraints, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of labels as an abstraction of attributes suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization aspect of finding a valid committee with the highest score suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of constraints and the fixed-parameter tractable algorithm suggest a connection to computational complexity and parameterized algorithms (cs.SI).
